# Conventional commit suggestion

When your work includes repository changes (code, config, docs, tests, tooling, or workflows),
include a one-line conventional commit suggestion at the end of your final reply in this format:

`type(scope): imperative description`

Use common types like `fix`, `feat`, `docs`, `ci`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`.
